{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:30:25.848125+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "---\n\n## How to run and build the React admin app\n\n**Tech stack:** Vite + React + TypeScript + MUI (Material UI).\n\n---\n\n### 1. Install dependencies\n\n```bash\nyarn install\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Run locally (development)\n\n```bash\nyarn dev\n```\n\n- Uses `NODE_ENV=local` → loads env from `envs/.env.local`.\n- Vite dev server starts on **port 10086** (defined in `.env.local` as `VITE_PORT = 10086`).\n- API base URL is `https://mock.local.lantron.ltd`.\n- The `--host` flag makes it accessible on your LAN.\n\nYou can also preview a **staging** dev server (different env, no `--host`):\n\n```bash\nyarn dev:stg\n```\n\n- Uses `NODE_ENV=stg` → loads `envs/.env.stg`.\n- API base URL: `https://mock.stg.lantron.ltd`.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Build for production\n\n| Command | Vite mode | Env file | API URL |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `yarn build` | `prod` | `envs/.env.prod` (NODE_ENV=prod) | `https://mock.lantron.ltd` |\n| `yarn build:stg` | `test` | `envs/.env.stg` (NODE_ENV=stg) | `https://mock.stg.lantron.ltd` |\n| `yarn build:prod` | `production` | `envs/.env.prod` (NODE_ENV=prod) | `https://mock.lantron.ltd` |\n\nAll builds output to the `dist/` directory (`VITE_OUTPUT_DIR = dist`).\n\n---\n\n### 4. Preview a production build\n\n```bash\nyarn serve\n```\n\nThis runs `vite preview --host`, which serves the contents of `dist/` as a static site (again on port 10086 if the env resolves there).\n\n---\n\n### 5. Deploy\n\n- **GitHub Pages:** `yarn deploy` — uses `gh-pages -d dist` to push the `dist/` folder to the `gh-pages` branch.\n- **Docker:** The `Dockerfile` does a multi-stage build:\n  1. Builds with `yarn && yarn build` (defaults to prod mode).\n  2. Copies `dist/` into an Nginx alpine image and serves on **port 80**.\n\n  ```bash\n  docker build -t my-admin-app .\n  docker run -p 8080:80 my-admin-app\n  ```\n\n---\n\n### 6. Code quality\n\n```bash\nyarn lint   # ESLint check\nyarn fix    # ESLint auto-fix\n```\n\n---\n\n### Environment files summary (`envs/` directory)\n\n| File | NODE_ENV | API Base |\n|---|---|---|\n| `.env.local` | local | `https://mock.local.lantron.ltd` |\n| `.env.stg` | stg | `https://mock.stg.lantron.ltd` |\n| `.env.prod` | prod | `https://mock.lantron.ltd` |\n\n> **Note:** Vite resolves env at build/dev time via the `vite.config.ts` logic — if no root `.env` exists, it picks up the matching `envs/.env.<NODE_ENV>` file. Path aliases `@` → `src/` and `@@` → project root are also configured in Vite.\n\n---\n\n### Full `package.json` scripts for reference\n\n```json\n{\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"dev\": \"cross-env NODE_ENV=local vite --host\",\n    \"dev:stg\": \"cross-env NODE_ENV=stg vite\",\n    \"serve\": \"vite preview --host\",\n    \"build\": \"vite build --mode prod\",\n    \"build:stg\": \"cross-env vite build --mode test\",\n    \"build:prod\": \"cross-env vite build --mode production\",\n    \"deploy\": \"gh-pages -d dist\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint --ext .jsx,.js,.ts,.tsx .\",\n    \"fix\": \"yarn lint --fix\"\n  }\n}\n```", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 953, "prompt_tokens": 7684, "total_tokens": 8637, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 26, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 6976, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0003854928, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0001186528, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00026684}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780871415-8SWywjCsHd41VUtZ8W91", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea435-452c-7061-ac99-0e1a83e7def7-